race.comment: WHISKY TRAIN (4) produced a much-improved effort last start when charging late to just miss the frame. Third-up now and stepping out over a longer journey, he looks ready to peak. LISSARO (14) has been hitting the line strongly, recording consecutive minor placings, including a narrow miss here last time over this trip. He'll get back again but expect him to be storming home late. WARRIOR BAE (7) continues to race consistently, beaten only a neck at Lismore last start. The wide draw makes life tougher, but his honesty keeps him in the mix. DA SILVA GOLD (9) is flying, having made it two wins on the bounce with a powerful finish at Ballina. Backing up quickly and stepping up in trip, he looks a genuine winning chance again.
